The paper deals with the analysis of RF propagation characteristics of a wireless sensor network, specifically the MICAz mote. This falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves measuring the Received Signal Strength Indicator (RSSI) which is related to Information Theory (cs.IT). The analysis involves changing the antenna orientation and distance between the nodes, which can be considered as a form of optimization and falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also deals with the effect of the ground on the RF propagation, which can be considered as a form of system dynamics and falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves the use of antennas, which is related to Electromagnetics (cs.EM).
